This paper deals with decision-making under uncertainty and regret-minimization, which are core topics in game theory (cs.GT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses dynamic decision problems, which are relevant to the fields of decision science (cs.DS) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
